When performing a REST call to GreenHopper API an invalid view is requested a NullPointerException results.  Should this be updated to produce the same response as the first example?

Example request and result when the request is poorly formed (missing auth credentials):
{code}curl -X GET  "https://<instance>/rest/greenhopper/1.0/rapid/charts/sprintreport?rapidViewId=1&sprintId=1"{code}

{noformat}{"errorMessages":["The requested board cannot be viewed because it either does not exist or you do not have permission to view it."],"errors":{}}{noformat}

Example request and result when the request is poorly formed (invalid report) and results in a NullPointerError:
{code}curl -D- -u <user>:<pass> -X GET -H "https://<instance>/rest/greenhopper/1.0/rapid/charts/sprintreport?rapidViewId=1"{code}

{noformat}
