Raised for [~mdoar]:

{quote}
I'd like to see an Admin tab for GH that would read an activeobjects.xml file and recreate the sprints in a supported way.
{quote}

To migrate Active Objects data for GreenHopper, it's slightly complicated:

{quote}
I wrote a Python script that used the GH REST API to extract information about sprints and their issues. Then a Script Runner groovy script read that data in and recreated the sprints in the new JIRA.
{quote}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Server*. Using *JIRA Software Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWCLOUD-8169].
  {panel}

According to our documentation on [Sprint Report|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/GH/Viewing+the+Sprint+Report]:
{quote}
For some issues, the Story Points are not shown in the Sprint Report. This is because the Sprint Report shows information initially included in the sprint – that is, what the team actually committed to. (That being said, if you add an issue with zero story points to a sprint, start the sprint and then change the Story Points, you will see the initial value in the Sprint Report.) If you would like to see all changes, switch to the Burndown Chart instead.
{quote}

However, if an issue is created with 0 Story Points, then 2 Story Points are added to it *before* the Sprint Start and *after* the start of the Sprint they Story Points are changed to 3, 0 Story Points are displayed on the Sprint Report.

I believe it should be 2.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Server*. Using *JIRA Software Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWCLOUD-8063].
  {panel}

The Atlassian way of handling sub issues is to only calculate their workload using time estimates. This is not how all teams work, and it would be nice to have an option on the board that lets you set if sub issues should be treated just like any other issue. This would broaden up the use of the rapid board for more of its users.

One problem with the current implementation is that story points on sub issues are not shown in the burndown chart. Any subissue is not shown in these charts at all. This makes statistics gathering somewhat hard to do if you treat issues in this way.

An added bonus would be if the combined value of the story points could be viewed on the parent issue as a calculated field. This calculated fields should not count towards the statistics of course.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Server*. Using *JIRA Software Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWCLOUD-8061].
  {panel}

